msgstr "Monks’ Confession 8"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:0.5"
msgid "8. Bhūtārocanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on telling truthfully"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.24, pts-cs-bu-pc8.1.1, pts-vp-en.2.208, ms2V_220
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Vesālī in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā sandiṭṭhā sambhattā bhikkhū vaggumudāya nadiyā tīre vassaṃ upagacchiṃsu."
msgstr "At that time a number of monks who were friends had entered the rains on the banks of the river Vaggumudā."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena vajjī dubbhikkhā hoti—dvīhitikā setaṭṭhikā salākāvuttā, na sukarā uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ."
msgstr "Just then Vajjī was short of food and afflicted with hunger, with crops blighted and turned to straw, and it was not easy to get by on almsfood."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.4"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—“etarahi kho vajjī dubbhikkhā—dvīhitikā setaṭṭhikā salākāvuttā, na sukarā uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ."
msgstr "The monks considered the difficult circumstances, and they thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.5"
msgid "Kena nu kho mayaṃ upāyena samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vaseyyāma, na ca piṇḍakena kilameyyāmā”ti?"
msgstr "“How can we remain united and in harmony, have a comfortable rains, and get almsfood without problems?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.6"
msgid "Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Some said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.7"
msgid "“handa mayaṃ, āvuso, gihīnaṃ kammantaṃ adhiṭṭhema."
msgstr "“We could do work for the lay people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.8"
msgid "Evaṃ te amhākaṃ dātuṃ maññissanti."
msgstr "and they’ll give something in return."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.9"
msgid "Evaṃ mayaṃ samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasissāma, na ca piṇḍakena kilamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "In this way we’ll be united and in harmony, and we’ll spend the rains in comfort and have no problems getting almsfood.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.10"
msgid "Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Some said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.11"
msgid "“alaṃ, āvuso, kiṃ gihīnaṃ kammantaṃ adhiṭṭhitena?"
msgstr "“There’s no need to do work for the lay people."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.12"
msgid "Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, gihīnaṃ dūteyyaṃ harāma."
msgstr "Let’s instead take messages for them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.13"
msgid "Evaṃ te amhākaṃ dātuṃ maññissanti."
msgstr "and they’ll give something in return."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.14"
msgid "Evaṃ mayaṃ samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasissāma, na ca piṇḍakena kilamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "In this way we’ll be united and in harmony, and we’ll spend the rains in comfort and have no problems getting almsfood.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.15"
msgid "Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Some said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.16"
msgid "“alaṃ, āvuso; kiṃ gihīnaṃ kammantaṃ adhiṭṭhitena."
msgstr "“There’s no need to do work for the lay people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.17"
msgid "Kiṃ gihīnaṃ dūteyyaṃ haṭena."
msgstr "nor to take messages for them."

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.209
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.18"
msgid "Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttarimanussadhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsissāma—"
msgstr "Let’s instead praise one another’s superhuman qualities to the lay people, "

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.19"
msgid "‘asuko bhikkhu paṭhamassa jhānassa lābhī, asuko bhikkhu dutiyassa jhānassa lābhī, asuko bhikkhu tatiyassa jhānassa lābhī, asuko bhikkhu catutthassa jhānassa lābhī, asuko bhikkhu sotāpanno, asuko bhikkhu sakadāgāmī, asuko bhikkhu anāgāmī, asuko bhikkhu arahā, asuko bhikkhu tevijjo, asuko bhikkhu chaḷabhiñño’ti."
msgstr "‘Such a monk has the first absorption, such a monk the second absorption, such a monk the third, such a monk the fourth; such a monk is a stream-enterer, such a monk a once-returner, such a non-returner, such a perfected one; such a monk has the three true insights, and such the six direct knowledges.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.20"
msgid "Evaṃ te amhākaṃ dātuṃ maññissanti."
msgstr "Then they’ll give to us."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.21"
msgid "Evaṃ mayaṃ samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasissāma, na ca piṇḍakena kilamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "In this way we’ll be united and in harmony, and we’ll spend the rains in comfort and have no problems getting almsfood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.22"
msgid "“Eso yeva kho, āvuso, seyyo, yo amhākaṃ gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttarimanussadhammassa vaṇṇo bhāsito”ti."
msgstr "Indeed, this is the better way, that we praise one another’s superhuman qualities to the lay people.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_221
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.23"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttarimanussadhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsiṃsu—"
msgstr "Then they praised each other’s superhuman qualities to the lay people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.24"
msgid "“asuko bhikkhu paṭhamassa jhānassa lābhī … pe … asuko bhikkhu chaḷabhiñño”ti."
msgstr "“Such a monk has the first absorption … such a monk has the six direct knowledges.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.25"
msgid "Atha kho te manussā—"
msgstr "And those people thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.26"
msgid "“lābhā vata no, suladdhaṃ vata no, yesaṃ no evarūpā bhikkhū vassaṃ upagatā, na vata no ito pubbe evarūpā bhikkhū vassaṃ upagatā, yathayime bhikkhū sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā”ti."
msgstr "“We’re fortunate that such monks have come to us for the rains. Such monks as these, who are virtuous and of good character, have never before entered the rains with us.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.27"
msgid "Te na tādisāni bhojanāni attanā bhuñjanti, mātāpitūnaṃ denti puttadārassa denti dāsakammakaraporisassa denti mittāmaccānaṃ denti ñātisālohitānaṃ denti yādisāni bhikkhūnaṃ denti."
msgstr "And they gave such food and drink to those monks that they did not even eat and drink themselves, or give to their parents, to their wives and children, to their slaves, servants, and workers, to their friends and companions, or to their relatives. "

#. VAR: sāyanti pivanti → attanā pivanti (bj, s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.28"
msgid "Na tādisāni khādanīyāni sāyanīyāni pānāni attanā khādanti sāyanti pivanti mātāpitūnaṃ denti puttadārassa denti dāsakammakaraporisassa denti mittāmaccānaṃ denti ñātisālohitānaṃ denti, yādisāni bhikkhūnaṃ denti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.1.29"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū vaṇṇavā ahesuṃ pīṇindriyā pasannamukhavaṇṇā vippasannachavivaṇṇā."
msgstr "In this way those monks became handsome, with rounded features, bright faces, and clear skin."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, pts-vp-pli4.25, pts-cs-bu-pc8.1.2, ms2V_222
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.1"
msgid "Āciṇṇaṃ kho panetaṃ vassaṃvuṭṭhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ."
msgstr "Now it was the custom for monks who had finished keeping the rains to go and see the Master."

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.210
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.2"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū vassaṃvuṭṭhā temāsaccayena senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena vesālī tena pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr "So when the rainy-season residence was completed and the three months had elapsed, those monks put their dwellings in order, took their bowls and robes, and departed for Vesālī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.3"
msgid "Anupubbena yena vesālī mahāvanaṃ kūṭāgārasālā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr "When they eventually arrived at Vesālī, they went to the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr "There they approached the Master, bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.5"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena disāsu vassaṃvuṭṭhā bhikkhū kisā honti lūkhā dubbaṇṇā uppaṇḍuppaṇḍukajātā dhamanisanthatagattā."
msgstr "At that time the monks who had completed the rainy-season residence in that region were thin, haggard and pale, their veins protruding all over their limbs."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.6"
msgid "Vaggumudātīriyā pana bhikkhū vaṇṇavā honti pīṇindriyā pasannamukhavaṇṇā vippasannachavivaṇṇā."
msgstr "But the monks from the banks of the Vaggumudā were handsome, with rounded features, bright faces, and clear skin."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.7"
msgid "Āciṇṇaṃ kho panetaṃ buddhānaṃ bhagavantānaṃ āgantukehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ paṭisammodituṃ."
msgstr "It is the custom for Buddhas to greet newly arrived monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.8"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā vaggumudātīriye bhikkhū etadavoca—"
msgstr "and so the Master said to them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.9"
msgid "“kacci, bhikkhave, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyaṃ, kacci samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasittha, na ca piṇḍakena kilamitthā”ti?"
msgstr "“I hope you’re keeping well, monks, I hope you’re comfortable; I hope you spent the rains at ease, in concord and harmony, without dispute, and that you had no trouble getting almsfood?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.10"
msgid "“Khamanīyaṃ, bhagavā, yāpanīyaṃ, bhagavā."
msgstr "“We’re keeping well, Master, we’re comfortable;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.11"
msgid "Samaggā ca mayaṃ, bhante, sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasimhā, na ca piṇḍakena kilamimhā”ti."
msgstr "we spent the rains at ease, in concord and harmony, without dispute, and we had no trouble getting almsfood.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.12"
msgid "Jānantāpi tathāgatā pucchanti, jānantāpi na pucchanti."
msgstr "Buddhas sometimes ask knowing, and knowing sometimes do not ask;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.13"
msgid "Kālaṃ viditvā pucchanti, kālaṃ viditvā na pucchanti."
msgstr "they ask knowing the right time to ask, and they ask knowing the right time not to ask."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.14"
msgid "Atthasañhitaṃ tathāgatā pucchanti, no anatthasañhitaṃ."
msgstr "Buddhas ask when it is beneficial, not when it is unbeneficial;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.15"
msgid "Anatthasañhite setughāto tathāgatānaṃ."
msgstr "in regard to what is unbeneficial, the Buddhas have destroyed the bridge."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.16"
msgid "Dvīhākārehi buddhā bhagavanto bhikkhū paṭipucchanti—"
msgstr "Buddhas question the monks for two reasons:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.17"
msgid "“dhammaṃ vā desessāma, sāvakānaṃ vā sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmā”ti."
msgstr "to give a teaching or to lay down a training rule."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_223
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.18"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā vaggumudātīriye bhikkhū etadavoca—"
msgstr "And the Master said to those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.19"
msgid "“yathā kathaṃ pana tumhe, bhikkhave, samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasittha, na ca piṇḍakena kilamitthā”ti?"
msgstr "“In what way, monks, did you spend the rains at ease, without having any trouble getting almsfood?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.20"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "And they told the Master what had happened."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.211
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.21"
msgid "“Kacci pana vo, bhikkhave, bhūtan”ti?"
msgstr "“But had you really achieved those superhuman qualities?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.22"
msgid "“Bhūtaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.23"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.24"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, bhikkhave, udarassa kāraṇā gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttarimanussadhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsissatha."
msgstr "“Monks, how can you for the sake of your stomachs praise one another’s superhuman qualities to lay people?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.25"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.26"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.26a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc5, ms2V_224
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:1.2.27"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu anupasampannassa uttarimanussadhammaṃ āroceyya bhūtasmiṃ, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk truthfully tells a person who is not fully ordained of a superhuman quality, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, pts-cs-bu-pc8.2.1, ms2V_225
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe … ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_226
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.5"
msgid "Anupasampanno nāma"
msgstr "A person who is not fully ordained:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.6"
msgid "bhikkhuñca bhikkhuniñca ṭhapetvā, avaseso anupasampanno nāma."
msgstr "anyone except a fully ordained monk and a fully ordained nun."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_227
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.7"
msgid "Uttarimanussadhammo nāma"
msgstr "A superhuman quality:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.8"
msgid "jhānaṃ, vimokkho, samādhi, samāpatti, ñāṇadassanaṃ, maggabhāvanā, phalasacchikiriyā, kilesappahānaṃ, vinīvaraṇatā cittassa, suññāgāre abhirati."
msgstr "absorption, release, stillness, attainment, knowledge and vision, development of the path, realization of the fruits, abandoning the defilements, a mind without hindrances, delighting in solitude."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.8a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.8b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h4><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_228
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.9"
msgid "Jhānanti"
msgstr "Absorption:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.10"
msgid "paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ, dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ, tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ, catutthaṃ jhānaṃ."
msgstr "the first absorption, the second absorption, the third absorption, the fourth absorption."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_229
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.11"
msgid "Vimokkhoti"
msgstr "Release:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.12"
msgid "suññato vimokkho, animitto vimokkho, appaṇihito vimokkho."
msgstr "emptiness release, signless release, desireless release."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.13"
msgid "Samādhīti"
msgstr "Stillness:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.14"
msgid "suññato samādhi, animitto samādhi, appaṇihito samādhi."
msgstr "emptiness stillness, signless stillness, desireless stillness."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.15"
msgid "Samāpattīti"
msgstr "Attainment:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.16"
msgid "suññatā samāpatti, animittā samāpatti, appaṇihitā samāpatti."
msgstr "emptiness attainment, signless attainment, desireless attainment."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, pts-vp-pli4.26, ms2V_232
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.17"
msgid "Ñāṇadassananti"
msgstr "Knowledge and vision:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.18"
msgid "tisso vijjā."
msgstr "the three true insights."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc14, ms2V_233
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc8:2.1.19"
msgid "Maggabhāvanāti"
msgstr "Development of the path:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
